22/09/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Interior Minister Ivica Dacic pledged on Tuesday (September 21st) that authorities will prove they are co-operating fully with The Hague war crimes tribunal, after criticism last week by tribunal chief prosecutor Serge Brammertz. Dacic said that while no arrests have been made, an increasing amount of evidence has been gathered and the investigation is steadily advancing. EU Enlargement. Full co-operation with the UN tribunal remains a condition for ratification of Serbia's Stabilisation and Association Agreement by the EU member states. (B92, Tanjug, Politika - 21/09/10)
